BT 1 0 0 1 0 86.5 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 16 TL 1.604437 Tw (Every action occurs within a specific moment. That moment contains variables \227 contextual, situational,) Tj T* 0 Tw .897145 Tw (human \227 that may differ materially from the conditions present when authority was originally granted. The) Tj T* 0 Tw .261279 Tw (human anchor may have lost the capacity to authorise. The conditions under which the original authorisation) Tj T* 0 Tw .836918 Tw (made sense may have changed. The consequence tier of the action may have escalated beyond what the) Tj T* 0 Tw .667591 Tw (original authority covered. Without re-evaluation at that moment, systems act on outdated assumptions that) Tj T* 0 Tw (may bear no relationship to current reality.) Tj T* ET
